news.title: Gurugram civic body imposes Rs 3.4 lakh fines for GRAP violations
news.para: Of this, Rs 1.4 lakh (41% of the penalty amount) was issued for carrying out construction activities, a major GRAP violation, especially when the air quality is consistently deteriorating.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 53-acre land in Joka, Kolkata
news.para: The proposed project is estimated to have a development potential of about 1.3 million sq ft of saleable area comprising primarily residential plotted development with an estimated revenue potential of Rs 500 crore.

news.title: Self-survey, facial recognition to be used in new survey for PMAY-G second phase: Sources
news.para: According to a source from the Rural Development Ministry, for the first time, facial recognition technology will be used for both surveyors and those surveyed to maintain transparency.

news.title: Authority starts survey of land to be acquired for new Noida
news.para: Noida CEO Lokesh M said, "We inspected the proposed land in the Sikandrabad area of Bulandshahr. We also inspected the land in Jokhabad village for a temporary office of the Noida Authority, which will supervise the land acquisition and development works in the area.

news.title: Telangana RERA imposes 18 lakh penalty on Sterling Homes for delays
news.para: The project, located in Mallampet Village of Medchal-Malkajgiri district, was originally scheduled for completion by July 1, 2023, with a grace period extending to Dec 2023

news.title: Telangana RERA orders Aliens Developers to complete project
news.para: The Authority also ordered the developer to pay interest at the rate of 10.95% per annum from Dec 2017 to the date of possession, excluding the Covid-19 waiver period, for delays in delivering the flat.

news.title: NCLT directs initiation of insolvency proceedings against Raheja Developers
news.para: The National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) has initiated insolvency proceedings against Raheja Developers following a petition by flat buyers in the Gurgaon-based Shilas project. The NCLT cited "debt due and default" by the company for its failure to deliver units on time despite receiving payments. An Interim Resolution Professional has been appointed as the case proceeds.

news.title: Bombay HC directs civic bodies to link their websites with Maharashtra RERA
news.para: "This integration would enable RERA to conduct real-time verification of commencement and occupation certificates, thereby preventing forgery and protecting consumers' interests in line with the RERA Act's objectives," said Chief Justice Devendra Kumar Upadhyaya and Justice Amit Borkar.

news.title: Odisha government distributes house allotment letters to 116 slum dwellers
news.para: A total of 116 beneficiaries received their allotment letters, including 47 for Chandrasekharpur AHP, 36 for Nilamadhab Awas AHP, and 28 for Subudhipur's Barunei Enclave AHP.

news.title: IIFL Home Finance to register Rs 1 trillion AUM in next 3-4 years: Gaurav Seth, CFO
news.para: IIFL Home Finance's CFO, Gaurav Seth outlines plans to achieve this ambitious growth through strategic partnerships, geographic expansion, and a focus on maintaining affordability for customers in challenging economic times.

news.title: Construction of new office space down by 4% in Q2 FY25: Vestian
news.para: Bengaluru’s share in absorption rose significantly from 25% in Q2 FY25 to 36% in Q3 FY25. And has 6.63 million sq ft absorption in Q3 FY25 while Hyderabad followed with 2.79 million sq ft. The share of Mumbai was reduced from 20% to 12% during the same period.

news.title: Deepika Padukone and Ranveer Singh rents apartment in Mumbai
news.para: The lease agreement, registered in November 2024, spans a tenure of 36 months and includes an initial security deposit of Rs 21 lakh, according to Square Yards.

news.title: Mining department officials crack down on illegal stone quarries in Jajpur
news.para: Jayaprakash Nayak, deputy director of mines (minor minerals), Jajpur, said during the operation, authorities seized two compressors and a boulder-laden tractor while shutting down all illegal mining activities in these hillocks.

news.title: BHIVE Workspace acquires 39,753 sq ft in Bengaluru from Century Real Estate for Rs 3.54 crore
news.para: The center, situated at HAL second stage area, Old Airport Road, Indiranagar, Bengaluru, has over 1,000 seats capacity.

news.title: Bengaluru: Residents frustrated over bad infrastructure seek MP’s help
news.para: In their letter to the Bangalore Rural MP, they highlighted the poor condition of roads, reliable and regular power supply, citing daily fluctuations and inadequate grid capacity.

news.title: SC orders to strictly enforce GRAP stage IV in NCR till further orders
news.para: "We make it clear that till further orders are passed by this court, implementation of stage 4 of GRAP will continue even if AQI level drops below 450," a bench of Justices Abhay S Oka and Augustine George Masih directed as it sought compliance reports from Delhi-NCR states and the Centre by Thursday.

news.title: Indore: Development work of Multi Modal logistic park to begin by end of 2024
news.para: MMLP is being established in a PPP (DBFOT) mode across 112.6 hectares near Pithampur in Dhar district, encompassing 90 hectare of private land from four villages and 22 hectares of government land.

news.title: China's Beijing, Shanghai announce tax breaks to boost property markets
news.para: Other major Chinese cities are widely expected to follow suit and the measures come on the heels of some tax breaks on home and land transactions unveiled by China's finance ministry last week.

news.title: Indore civic body demolishes illegal portions of 63 houses for road widening
news.para: Senior IMC officials said notices informing residents about the impending demolition of unauthorized extensions to their property were issued a week ago. As several residents failed to comply with the notice, the civic body decided to launch the demolition drive on Monday.

news.title: Karnataka govt faces Rs 76 crore legal notice from Adani Group over unsold Malaysian sand
news.para: The Krishnapatnam Port Company (KPCL), owned by Adani Group, has issued legal notices, demanding compensation of Rs 76 crore towards uncleared stocks worth Rs 10 crore.
